Oregon Talent Council might be interested in coinvesting with us on this. Have asked me to testify in front of their council in Wilsonville next week. TBD if I can make it on a number of calendar factors.

Biz Oregon meeting (before ahm) was good too. Heather Stafford is heading to Ireland - they’re interested in funding something of this sort. There’s an ex-Intel guy from out there (Joel might know him) who is trying to set up a $100 million IoT fund here in Oregon.
They also offered us the Wapato jail as a place to grow PMMC into.

Also JP at site works mentioned something called "digital thread." The idea is that a design can be purchased and fabricated anywhere. For example, something designed in Germany can be CNC'd in Portland rather than fabricated in German then shipped over. He mentioned their CNC was set up to do this. This is something we should look more into
Neat. Good lead Lee.
Heard back from my ARM IoT guy. Meeting with him on Monday. Would love to show him a sommely cap and chat PMMC.
Awesome
Apparently Digital Thread is a guideline <https://www.nist.gov/programs-projects/digital-thread-smart-manufacturing>

attachments.title: Digital Thread for Smart Manufacturing
attachments.text: Objective - The Digital Thread for Smart Manufacturing Systems project will deliver methods and protocols that extend and complete the digital thread for information running through design, manufacturing and product support processes enabling easy integration of smart manufacturing systems. The results of this project will accelerate the design to production timeline at
